## Use Cases

### 1. Summer-to-Winter Storage Strategy
```
Scenario: Buy cheap gas in summer, store, sell in winter

Example:
- Inject: July 1, 2025 @ $11.42/MMBtu
- Withdraw: January 31, 2025 @ $11.84/MMBtu
- Spread: $0.42/MMBtu
- Storage Cost: $3.07/MMBtu (7 months)
- Net P&L: -$2.71/MMBtu

Note: 2025 is a low-volatility year; historically offers better spreads
```

### 2. Storage Contract Pricing
```
Use case: Warehouse operator pricing storage capacity

Input: Expected injection and withdrawal dates
Output: Required spread to cover storage costs + profit margin

Calculation:
Minimum Spread = Storage Cost + Operator Margin
Storage Cost = $0.50/MMBtu/month × months held
```

### 3. Risk Management
```
Use case: Hedging seasonal exposure

Tool: Use daily price estimates to value forward contracts
Benefit: Granular pricing vs. only having monthly snapshots
```

### 4. Portfolio Analysis
```
Use case: Evaluate natural gas holdings

Features:
- Estimate value at any date
- Project future valuations
- Identify seasonal risks
```

